<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1799,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,1871,1896]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Species recognition.</emphasis>
Abdominal tergites plain brown; tergite six lacking posterior row of strong setae. Oviscape with long dorsomedian process. Ventral sclerite of oviscape elongate. This species is most similar to the other North American species, 
<taxonomicName box="[435,618,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Apocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="missouriensis">
<emphasis box="[435,618,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">A. missouriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by characters given in the key.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,838,1734,1757]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281919/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="23" targetBox="[165,1398,196,1704]" targetPageId="4">
